[1] China - China National Health Commission 8 Feb 2020
Date: Sun 9 Feb 2020
Source: China National Health Commission [in Chinese, machine trans., edited]
http://www.nhc.gov.cn/xcs/yqtb/202002/4f28ab5ca87d42d284833df3ccc8d45a.shtml


Update on the epidemic situation of new coronavirus pneumonia as of 24:00 8 Feb 2020
-------------------------------------------------------------------
At 04:00 on [8 Feb 2020], 31 provinces (autonomous regions, municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps reported that 2656 confirmed cases (2147 cases in Hubei) were newly added, 87 severe cases (52 cases in Hubei) were newly added, and there were 89 deaths (81 in Hubei, 2 in Henan, 1 each in Hebei, Heilongjiang, Anhui, Shandong, Hunan, and Guangxi), and 3916 suspected new cases (2067 in Hubei).

On the same day, 600 new patients were discharged from hospital (324 in Hubei), and 31 124 close contacts were lifted from medical observation.

As of 24:00 on [8 Feb 2020], according to reports from 31 provinces (autonomous regions and municipalities) and the Xinjiang Production and Construction Corps, there were 33 738 confirmed cases (including 6188 severe cases), and a total of 2649 discharged patients recovered (Heilongjiang reduced one). A total of 811 deaths have been reported, 37 198 confirmed cases have been reported (1 in each of Shanxi, Heilongjiang, Henan, and Hainan), and there are currently 28 942 suspected cases. A total of 371 905 close contacts have been traced, and 188 183 close contacts remain in medical observation.

A total of 53 confirmed cases were reported in Hong Kong, Macao, and Taiwan: 26 in the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (1 death), 10 in the Macao Special Administrative Region (1 case recovered and discharged), and 17 in Taiwan (1 case recovered and discharged).

--
