[A total of 2656 newly confirmed cases have been reported by China in the past 24 hours, compared with 3399 during the similar time frame [6-7 Feb 2020]. This brings the total number of reported confirmed cases to 37 198. 89 deaths were reported in this time period, bringing the total number of reported deaths to 811. In the past 24 hours there has been 1 newly confirmed case reported from Taiwan.

There has been a significant decrease (21.9%) in the number of newly confirmed cases reported by China in the past 24 hours. It awaits to be seen if there will be a continued decrease in reported cases or if this was an observed anomaly attributable to other reasons (reduced laboratory capacity for example.)

A good map of China showing provinces can be found at https://www.chinadiscovery.com/china-maps/china-provincial-map.html and a HealthMap/ProMED-mail map at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6969995,155. - Mod.MPP]

