[4] Selected media reports of transmission outside mainland China
A. France ex Singapore
Date: Sat 8 Feb 2020
Source: The Telegraph [edited]
https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2020/02/08/coronavirus-uk-news-latest-virus-outbreak-china/


The country's health minister has said 5 British people have been diagnosed with coronavirus in France after being infected during a skiing holiday. The victims, one of whom is a child, were staying in the same ski resort chalet and were infected when one of the group came into contact with someone who had been in Singapore, Agnes Buzyn said this morning [8 Feb 2020]. They are in a stable condition and being constantly monitored at an unnamed hospital in the eastern Haute-Savoie Alpine region of south eastern France.

The British person who brought the infection back from Singapore arrived in France on [24 Jan 2020] and stayed at the ski resort of Contamines Montjoie for 4 days.

